Arjun
HTTP parameter discovery tool

Web Application
Description
Arjun finds hidden HTTP parameters in web applications. It uses a huge default dictionary and smart techniques to discover parameters not visible in the UI.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which arjun
Install command:

pip install arjun
Basic Syntax
arjun -u <url>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
arjun -u http://target.com/page

Discover parameters	Find hidden params	
arjun -u http://target.com/page -m POST

POST parameters	Test POST requests	
arjun -u http://target.com/page -m JSON

JSON parameters	Test JSON bodies	
arjun -u http://target.com/page -w custom.txt

Custom wordlist	Use specific params	
arjun -i urls.txt

Multiple URLs	Batch testing	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Identify target endpoint
2
Run arjun
3
Review discovered parameters
4
Test each for vulnerabilities
5
Use with sqlmap/xsstrike
Understanding the Output
Lists discovered parameters with their detected type (GET/POST/JSON).

Important Warnings
•
Can generate many requests
•
May trigger WAF
•
Use on authorized targets only
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
